        "content": "<p>bjorn3 opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13180\">PR #13180</a> from <code>bjorn3:cranelift_jit_memory_cleanup</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This was previously not done with the theory that using the regular heap allocator could be faster. We now have an arena memory provider and using mmap is necessary anyway when SELinux is enabled. I don't think the benefits outweight the code complexity cost. Also use memmap2 on Windows too in cranelift-jit.</p>\n<p>Fixes <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/4986\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/issues/4986</a></p>\n</blockquote>",
